import re
custom_stopwords = {'no', 'not', 'never', 'none', 'nobody', 'nothing', 'neither', 
                      'nowhere', "isn't", "aren't", "wasn't", "weren't", "doesn't", 
                      "don't", "didn't", "can't", "couldn't", "won't", "wouldn't", 
                      "shouldn't", "hasn't", "haven't", "hadn't"}

corpus =[]
ps = PorterStemmer()
stop_words = set(stopwords.words("english")) - custom_stopwords #removinf all the default negative words

for i in range(len(data)):
    review=re.sub("[^a-zA-Z]"," ",data["Review"][i])
    review= review.lower()
    review= review.split()
    review = [ps.stem(word) for word in review if word not in stop_words]
    review = " ".join(review)
    corpus.append(review) #appending all the reviews in the empty corpus list
In [40]:
data["processed_text"]=corpus #creating new column for adding corpus list

import re
import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import ttk
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from nltk.stem import PorterStemmer
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
import joblib
import nltk

# Ensure that the stopwords are downloaded
nltk.download('stopwords')

class RestaurantReviewApp:
    def __init__(self, master):
        self.master = master
        master.title("Restaurant Review Classification App")
        master.geometry("400x300")  # Set a custom size for the window

        # Load your pre-trained Random Forest model and CountVectorizer
        try:
            self.model = joblib.load('Restaurant_review_model.pkl')  # Correct extension
            print("Model loaded successfully")
            self.vectorizer = joblib.load('count_v_res.pkl')  # Correct extension
            print("Vectorizer loaded successfully")
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Error loading model or vectorizer: {e}")
            self.model = None
            self.vectorizer = None

        # Create and set up widgets
        title_font = ('Helvetica', 16, 'bold')  # Larger font for the title
        self.label = ttk.Label(master, text="Enter your restaurant review:", font=title_font)
        self.label.pack(pady=10)

        self.text_entry = tk.Text(master, height=5, width=40)
        self.text_entry.pack(pady=10)

        # Create a button to classify
        self.classify_button = ttk.Button(master, text="Classify", command=self.classify_review)
        self.classify_button.pack(pady=10)

        self.result_label = ttk.Label(master, text="")
        self.result_label.pack(pady=10)

        # Style configuration for the button (using `map` for background/foreground)
        self.style = ttk.Style()
        self.style.configure('Custom.TButton', font=('Helvetica', 12), padding=(10, 5))
        self.style.map('Custom.TButton', foreground=[('pressed', 'black'), ('active', 'white')],
                       background=[('pressed', '!disabled', '#45a049'), ('active', '#4CAF50')])

        self.classify_button.config(style='Custom.TButton')

    def preprocess_text(self, text):
        custom_stopwords = {'don', "don't", 'ain', 'aren', "aren't", 'couldn', "couldn't",
                            'didn', "didn't", 'doesn', "doesn't", 'hadn', "hadn't", 'hasn', "hasn't",
                            'haven', "haven't", 'isn', "isn't", 'ma', 'mightn', "mightn't", 'mustn', "mustn't",
                            'needn', "needn't", 'shan', "shan't", 'no', 'nor', 'not', 'shouldn', "shouldn't",
                            'wasn', "wasn't", 'weren', "weren't", 'won', "won't", 'wouldn', "wouldn't"}

        ps = PorterStemmer()
        stop_words = set(stopwords.words("english")) - custom_stopwords

        review = re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]', ' ', text)
        review = review.lower()
        review = review.split()
        review = [ps.stem(word) for word in review if word not in stop_words]
        review = " ".join(review)

        return review

        if self.model is None or self.vectorizer is None:
            self.result_label.config(text="Model or vectorizer not loaded correctly.")
            return

        if user_input:
            processed_input =
